cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.ED, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper describes an interactive system for teaching basic proof methods in discrete mathematics, which involves automated theorem proving and first-order formulas. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the system uses automated theorem provers to check proof obligations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the system is implemented in Haskell. 
- cs.ED (Education) is another possibility as the system is designed for teaching purposes and has been tested by students. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the system has a web interface and can be accessed from the command line.
